!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

lack /læk/

(lacking,lacked,lacks) 

1. N-UNCOUNT If there is a lack of something, there is not enough of it or it does not exist at all. 缺乏; 不存在 [also 'a' N, usu N 'of' n] 

例： Despite his lack of experience, he got the job. 尽管缺乏经验，他还是得到了那份工作。 

例： The charges were dropped for lack of evidence. 由于缺少证据，起诉被撤销了。 

2. V-T/V-I If you say that someone or something lacks a particular quality or that a particular quality is lacking in them, you mean that they do not have any or enough of it. 缺乏; 没有 

例： It lacked the power of the Italian cars. 它没有意大利汽车那样的动力。 

例： He lacked the judgment and political acumen for the post of chairman. 他缺少作为主席的判断力和政治敏锐性。 

3. PHRASE If you say there is no lack of something, you are emphasizing that there is a great deal of it. 不缺某物 [强调] 

例： He said there was no lack of things for them to talk about. 他说他们不缺话题谈。

</div>

